headline: Three models bullish on broad indices; outcomes pending market close
summary: All three AI models (GPT-4o, Grok, Perplexity) predicted upside for SPY today, driven by positive pre-market sentiment and economic data. Tech stocks QQQ and individual names like AMD and KEYS showed particular strength in pre-market trading. However, actual closing prices remain unavailable, making it impossible to score predictions at this time.

consensus_picks.note: Perfect consensus across all three models on S&P 500 upside, citing pre-market futures strength and Fed rate cut expectations.
Two models bullish on tech-heavy Nasdaq-100, supported by strong earnings reports and major Meta 6G GPU deal announcement.
Both models saw Tesla weakness from regulatory scrutiny, though with modest confidence levels (0.55-0.60).

best_call.summary: Perplexity identified Keysight's exceptional 23.05% pre-market surge with highest confidence (0.75), backed by strong Q1 results and analyst upgrades.

worst_call.summary: Grok's TSLA downside call carries the lowest confidence among all predictions (0.55), with vague regulatory concerns and mixed social sentiment providing weak conviction.
